  "prompt": "What are the chances that a Spider Solitaire deal is winnable for 1/2/4 suits, assuming optimized play?",
  "response": "Spider Solitaire is a popular card game that is often played with different levels of difficulty, usually denoted by the number of suits involved. The winnability of a Spider Solitaire deal can vary significantly depending on the number of suits in play and the skill of the player.\n\n### 1 Suit:\nWith only one suit in play, Spider Solitaire is generally considered to be much easier and higher win rates are achievable. Most players can win the majority of deals with optimized play. The win rate is often estimated at around 98% or higher with optimal strategy. Most deals are winnable given enough patience and skill.\n\n### 2 Suits:\nWith two suits, the difficulty increases but many deals are still winnable. The win rate with optimized play is usually estimated to be around 75-85%. Two suits require more strategic planning in organizing columns and managing sequences of cards.\n\n### 4 Suits:\nWith the maximum difficulty of four suits, the game becomes significantly harder. The win rate is much lower, typically estimated to be around 50-60% with optimized play. Four suits require the highest level of skill, careful planning, and often some luck. The complexity increases as players must manage sequences of cards across four different suits.\n\nTo summarize:\n- **1 Suit**: ~98% winnable with optimized play\n- **2 Suits**: ~75-85% winnable with optimized play\n- **4 Suits**: ~50-60% winnable with optimized play\n\nThese estimations are based on the assumption of playing with an optimal strategy. Individual win rates may vary based on the player's experience and skill level.",
